Buying Panel Extract – Field Exclusion Note (LOCD20)
Summary
During development of the Buying Panel extracted entities, the field LOCD20 was referenced in the architect’s original SQL specification.
However, detailed investigation confirmed that LOCD20 does not exist in the Buying Panel source table (OEP20UX) in any of the available libraries.

Findings
A full system-wide column scan was performed across all accessible libraries.
This confirmed:

LOCD20 exists in multiple logistics, depot, warehouse, finance and route‑planning tables  
(e.g., FAP20, DYP20, OEP20A, ROUTE1AUL, LIBIA, LIBIPD, AULT1F3, AULT2F3, etc.)

LOCD20 does NOT exist in OEP20UX, which is the correct table for Buying Panel Extra List logic.

The architect’s SQL appears to have mixed fields from OEP20A (logistics) with OEP20UX (Buying Panel).

OEP20A and OEP20UX are different tables with different business purposes.

Conclusion
Because LOCD20 is a logistics location field and not part of the Buying Panel domain, and because it is not present in OEP20UX, the field has been excluded from the Buying Panel extract.

Impact
No loss of Buying Panel functionality

No impact on rule/list/item logic

No impact on customer eligibility

Prevents incorrect joins and invalid DataStage metadata

Ensures the extract reflects the true structure of the Buying Panel tables

Recommendation
If LOCD20 is required for a future enhancement, the business must confirm:

Which table the field should come from (OEP20A, DYP20, FAP20, etc.)

Whether it is actually part of the Buying Panel domain

Which library contains the authoritative version of the required table

Until that confirmation is provided, LOCD20 remains out of scope for the Buying Panel extract.